Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_case_an...cg_propagation(25.10)  timing_case_an...cg_propagation(25.10)

Name
       timing_case_analysis_for_icg_propagation

Syntax
       timing_case_analysis_for_icg_propagation

       {false | require_seq_prop | always | case_only | constant_only}

       Default: false

       Controls  whether  constants,  which  propagate to the inputs of  inte-
       grated clock gating (ICG) cells, are further propagated to  the  output
       pins of these cells. The ICG cells typically contain an internal regis-
       ter  or  latch structure which synchronizes the devices' enable signal.
       If a constant propagates to this enable, it can be  selectively  propa-
       gated  through  the  internal  sequential element to the related output
       pins.

       This global setting can uniquely control  the  handling  of  sequential
       propagation  through  ICG cells, or it can work in conjunction with the
       more  general  timing_case_analysis_for_sequential_propagation   global
       variable or setAnalysisMode -sequentialConstProp settings.

       The  constants  can be present in the analysis due to several different
       reasons, broadly breaking down to netlist constants and case  analysis.
       The  netlist constants come from connections to tie-hi or tie-lo cells,
       a 1'b0/1'b1 assignment in the netlist, or explicit power  rail  connec-
       tions.  The  constants  derived from these sources are considered to be
       immutable. The constants due to case analysis come  strictly  from  the
       set_case_analysis  constraint and are considered to be temporary - con-
       figuring the analysis to align to a certain mode.  You  may  choose  to
       handle  constants  from any source in a similar manner or customize the
       handling based on the constant type.

       If you choose to allow propagation of only a specific type of constant,
       the output pin's state function must resolve to a constant by only con-
       sidering inputs pins with the required constant  type.  Otherwise,  the
       constant will not be propagated.

       The  propagation  of constants to the output of a sequential device may
       affect how the timing checks on related input pins are analyzed. If all
       the possible transitions on a given input pin are unable to change  the
       constant  state  of  the output pin, the timing checks on the input pin
       will be disabled by default.

       Changing the state of this global variable will change where  constants
       are present in the analysis, typically resulting in sets of timing arcs
       and timing checks being enabled or disabled. As a result, a full timing
       update, including a

       fresh  delay  calculation,  will be initiated when this setting is tog-
       gled.

       You can use one of the following options:

       Option Description

       false  Disables sequential propagation from any  constant  source  (de-
              fault setting).

       require_seq_prop
              When  specified, the software will defer ICG sequential propaga-
              tion handling to what is more generally set for  all  sequential
              devices,   via   either   the   timing_case_analysis_for_sequen-
              tial_propagation global variable or the related  setAnalysisMode
              -sequentialConstProp  mode  setting.  For all the other options,
              the state of these external settings is not consequential.

       always Allows sequential propagation from any constant source - netlist
              or constraint-based.

       constant_only
              Allows sequential propagation only for constants that are due to
              the propagation of netlist-based constants.

       case_only
              Allows sequential propagation only for constants that are due to
              the   propagation    of    constraint-based    constants    from
              set_case_analysis settings.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

Related Information
              * setAnalysisMode

              * timing_case_analysis_for_sequential_propagation

